          _key18:
            "\n   #### hand  \n     \n   - You can define a page to bind to this node.\n   - There is a Save() function inside the page, which is triggered when the user clicks the [Save] button or [Send] button on the toolbar outside the frame.\n   - You need to complete the data integrity validation and data saving in the Save() function.\n   - If the save succeeds, return true, if the save fails, return false. e.g.: when the user performs a send, first perform the save, after the save succeeds, perform the send, after the save fails, block the send.\n   - The Url you enter can have parameters, but the system will attach all the parameters to that url.\n   - for example:/SDKFlowDemo/QingJia/SDKQianRuFangShiForm.htm 。\n   - For example: you configure the url as http://xxxx:222:/abc.htm The actual Url of the system is http://xxxx:222:/abc.htm?FK_Flow=xxx&FK_Node=xxx&WorkID=xxx&UserNo=xxx&Token=xxx\n   - The system will pass the variables and parameters of the current process environment to your custom page, you can display according to these parameters, save the data, control the data read-only, editable.\n   - If you use an absolute path you can use ccbpm's global variable @SDKFromServHost, e.g.: @SDKFromServHost/MyFile.htm\n    \n     ",
