          _key3: 'Synchronisation to built-in API interfaces',
          _key30:
            '\n #### Help\n - To select the synchronization mode. ccbpm provides three synchronization modes. \n - Please read each mode carefully. \n #### Synchronizing to a data source \n - Select a data source, or configure one if it is not in the list. \n - Select the table to be synchronized \n - After that the process fields are synchronized with the table fields. \n #### Synchronize to a custom API\n - Enter an API address. \n - The system will then synchronize the process run data to this address. \n #### Synchronize to Built-in API\n - The system provides a built-in API interface to which the system writes data according to the set synchronization time point. \n - You can override this interface to write the data to the specified location. \n ',
          _key31:
            '\n ### Help\n - Please enter the API address.\n - Format: `http://xxx.xxx.xxxx`\n\n ### Write Data Description \n- The system will pass the process `Master Table Data`, `Slave Table Data`, `Slave Table Attachment Data`, `Table Attachment Attachment Data` into your interface as a JSON.\n- You need to receive this JSON data entity to process it. \n- The following is a JSON example:\n\n```json\n{\n  "mainTable": {\n    "Emps": "",\n    "FK_DeptName": "Group Headquarters",\n    "FK_NY": "2024-11",\n    "SQDept": "Group Headquarters",\n    "SQR": "admin",\n    "SQRQ": "2024-11-20",\n    "ChuFaShiQiDong": "4324",\n    "QingJiaYuanYin": "6565",\n    "QingJiaLeiXing": "1",\n    "oid": "1853315159"\n  },\n  "dtls": [\n    {\n      "dtlNo": "ND401MingXiBiao",\n      "dtl": [\n        {\n          "dtlData": {\n            "ZiDuan1": "666",\n            "ZiDuan2": "777",\n            "Idx": "0"\n          },\n          "dtlAths": []\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  "aths": [\n    {\n      "attachmentid": "ND401_QJCLTJ",\n      "athdb": {\n        "fileFullName": "D%3A%5CJFlow2024%5Cjflow-web%5Csrc%5Cmain%5Cwebapp%5CDataUser%2FUploadFile%5CND401%5C%2F1853315159%2Fbe4b3ad8a85740df950bd029bf46d055.pdf",\n        "fileName": "NewPortableDocument1.pdf",\n        "sort": "",\n        "fileExts": "pdf",\n        "rdt": "11-20 10:42",\n        "myPK": "be4b3ad8a85740df950bd029bf46d055",\n        "refPKVal": "1853315159",\n        "rec": "admin",\n        "recName": "admin",\n        "fk_dept": "100",\n        "fk_deptName": "Group Headquarters"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n#### JSON Description\n- `mainTable` The main table data, which contains the values of the fields in the form and the values of the system fields.\n- `dtls` is a collection of slave table data.\n- `aths` is a collection of attachment data, note that the full path of the attachment (`fileFullName`) is URL-encoded and needs to be decoded when received.\n\n#### URL decoding NetCore\n```c#\nSystem.Net.WebUtility.UrlDecode(fileFullName);\n```\n#### URL decoding JAVA\n```java\nimport cn.hutool.json.JSONObject;\nimport cn.hutool.json.JSONUtil;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.SortedMap;\nimport java.util.TreeMap;\n/**\n * Example of Java Receive API\n * Note: The following code is for reference only.\n */\n@RestController\npublic class TestController {\n\n    @PostMapping("/testReceive")\n    @ResponseBody\n    public Object testReceive(@RequestBody Map<String,Object> map){\n        System.out.println(map);\n        JSONObject obj = JSONUtil.parseObj(map);\n        JSONObject mainTable = obj.getJSONObject("mainTable"); //Master Table Data\n        JSONArray dtls = obj.getJSONArray("dtls"); //Slave Table Data Collection\n        JSONArray aths = obj.getJSONArray("aths"); //Annex data sets\n        if(!aths.isEmpty()){\n            String fileFullName = aths.getJSONObject(0).getJSONObject("athdb").getStr("fileFullName");\n            java.net.URLDecoder.decode(fileFullName, "UTF-8"); //URL decoding\n        }\n        SortedMap<Object, Object> sortedMap = new TreeMap<Object, Object>() {\n            private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n            {\n                put("message", "Implementation success");\n                put("code", 200);\n                put("data", JSONUtil.toJsonStr(JSONUtil.parseObj(map)));\n                put("msg", "");\n            }};\n        return JSONUtil.toJsonStr(sortedMap);\n    }\n}\n```\n',
