            "\n #### Help \n - The SQL is required to return No,Name two columns, respectively the personnel number, personnel name, the returned data must be in order. \n - SQL statement support ccbpm expression, e.g. SELECT No,Name FROM Port_Emp WHERE FK_Dept='@WebUser.DeptNo'\n - e.g. SELECT No,Name FROM Port_Emp WHERE FK_Dept='@ MyFieldName' MyFieldName must be a node form field. \n - What is ccbpm expression, please baidu: ccbpm expression. \n - Note: 1. case sensitive. 2. order can not be changed, No,Name \n #### Other 1\n - Complex, commonly used sql, you can use 'Calculate by set SQLTempate to get recipients' . \n #### Other 2\n - If queue mode SQL statement is written: SELECT No,Name FROM Port_Emp WHERE FK_Dept='@WebUser.DeptNo' ORDER BY Idx \n - Idx is the sequence number . \n \n",
          _key113:
            '\n #### Help \n - For frequently used, complex receiver scenarios expressed in sql, saved and callable on other nodes. \n - When the SQL template changes, other nodes follow. It is a referencing relationship, not a copying relationship. \n - Scenario: Developer configures the rules so that business people can call them. \n #### Technical Information \n - Data is stored inside wf_sqltemplate. \n - Can be maintained manually. \n',
          _key114: '\n \n #### Help \n - This method is related to split and merge streams and only makes sense if the current node is a child thread.\n      \n',
          _key115:
            '\n#### RECIPIENT RULES - FREE SELECTION \n\n- This mode relies on the subjective selection of the sender from the previous node, not on automatic calculation. \n- In "Choice" mode, you are free to choose anyone as a receiver. As you can see in the figure below, you can search in the `common person selector`. \n- For example, when node A sends to node B, if node B recipient rules are selected by A, this operates similarly to sending an email - i.e. the approval message is sent to whomever you select. \n- **Load Node Default Recipients**: when this option is enabled, the recipients of the current node will default to the person selected below, but can still be adjusted or additional recipients can be added when sending. This feature needs to be used in conjunction with the Person Selection feature below. \n - When "Load Node Default Recipients" is enabled, please specify the recipients to be loaded by default in the personnel selection box. \n\n#### Generic Personnel Selector Schematic \n\n- ! [Enter image caption](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/AccepterRole/Img/BySelected.png "Screenshot.png")\n \n',
          _key116:
            '\n #### Help \n - Node A sends to node B if the recipient rule of node B is selected by A. Such behaviour is similar to the send mail mode, that is, I send to whoever I choose. \n - This mode has the subjective judgement of the sender of the previous node, rather than automatic calculation. \n - Fixed Range Selection: This is where you need to set the range of people to select, e.g. by SQL, Department, Personnel set to select just the Deputy Director, Deputy Minister. \n #### Fixed Range Personnel Selector Effect Diagram \n - ! [Enter image description](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/AccepterRole/Img/BySelectedFix.png "Screenshot.png")\n \n',
          _key117:
            '\n #### Help \n - Selecting contacts from other organisations is sending to whoever the user chooses. \n - This mode has a subjective judgement of the sender of the previous node, not an automatic calculation. \n #### Fixed range person selector effect image \n - ! [Enter image caption](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/AccepterRole/Img/BySelectedFix.png "Screenshot.png")\n \n',
          _key118:
            '\n #### Help \n - is controlled by the value of the enumeration field in the fill-in form, depending on the value of the corresponding enumeration field, different people are handled differently so that the behaviour is routed using this field. \n - Configuration of field name: field ID (example: leave type enumeration field, corresponding field ID is QJLX)\n - Configuration format: @ + enumeration key + , + person account No (example: @0,admin)\n \n',
          _key119:
            '\n\n #### Help \n - The URL is clicked to send a direct pop-up page for customised personnel selection, which requires the developer to save the recipient information into the WF_SelectAccepter table. \n - The system will pass the information of the current node into your url, such as: FK_Node,WorkID,FK_Flow\n - After selecting the user, you need to store the user ID of the selected user into the interface. \n\n #### DEMO \n - /DataUser/PopSelf.htm\n \n',
          _key12: 'Sectoral scope rules',
