            '\n \n #### Help \n - Please set up webpai, click webApi setup button. \n - Return data format: zhangsan,lisi,wangwu\n - Multiple persons separated by comma. \n \n',
          _key121: '\n #### Help \n - The form captures the department number, find the department head by department number. \n - Department Table:Port_Dept Head Field Leader\n',
          _key122:
            '\n#### Help \n - What is captured in the form is the post number, according to the post number the personnel under that post. \n - Position Table:Port_Station Position Personnel Department Correspondence Table:Port_DeptEmpStation \n - In ccbpm position and role are the same concept. \n#### only by role. \n- All personnel under the role as recipients. \n\n#### Intelligent Calculation by Role \n- First look for the set of people with that role from the department of the logged in person, if not found, then look at the higher level of the current department. \n- Any level found, the personnel are used as a drop-in. \n- If the search reaches the root directory and is still not found, the system throws an exception. \n- For a more detailed description of the algorithm, refer to the Intelligent Calculation by Job description. \n',
          _key123:
            '\n #### Help \n - When designing the node form, please add a field for personnel information (e.g. "Head of Department") that will be used as the designated recipient of this node. \n #### Running Diagrams\n - ! [Enter image description](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/AccepterRole/Img/EmpsField.png "Screenshot.png")\n \n',
          _key124:
            '\n \n #### Help \n - For split and merge scenarios where the previous node of the current node is a split node, and the current node is a sub-thread valid. \n - The previous node collects the receiver information from the table and uses it as the receiver of the current node. \n - This method is related to Triage and only makes sense if the current node is a child thread. \n - The current parameter is the field column of the detail table, if it is not filled in, it defaults to UserNo. \n \n',
