          _key16: '\n #### help\n - Show as many people as are bound. \n ',
          _key17:
            '\n #### Help \n - The people selector that pops up lists only the people in this department, including part-time departments. \n - For organizational chart, please refer to doc.ccbpm.co.uk manual. \n ',
          _key18: '\n #### Help \n - Based on the set of roles selected, find out the set of people under that set. \n - Lists the set of people for the user to choose from. \n ',
          _key19:
            '\n #### Help \n\n - The intersection of the set of people based on the set of departments (a person may be in more than one department) and the set of people under the selected role is the set of people to select. \n\n ',
          _key2: 'Limit the range by organizational structure',
          _key20: '\n #### Help \n - the set of people by binding, as a selectable object.     \n',
          _key21: '\n#### Help \n - Interface return value type is of type String, multiple persons separated by comma. \n - Format: zhangsan,lisi,wangwu\n',
          _key22:
            "\n \n #### Help \n - SQL is divided into two parts, departmental grouping, personnel list SQL \n - Departmental SQL grouping needs to return No,Name columns, respectively, departmental number, departmental name. \n - Department SQL supports ccbpm expressions, e.g. SELECT No,Name FROM Port_Dept.\n - The Personnel SQL is required to return No,Name,FK_Dept three columns, which are Personnel No., Personnel Name, and Departmental Code The data returned must be in order. \n - Personnel SQL statements support ccbpm expressions, e.g.: SELECT No,Name,FK_Dept FROM Port_Emp WHERE FK_Dept='@WebUser.DeptNo'\n - e.g.: SELECT No,Name,FK_Dept FROM Port_Emp WHERE FK_Dept='@MyFieldName' MyFieldName can be a node form field. \n - If the process is initiated through the api interface, you can pass in system parameters SELECT No,Name,FK_Dept FROM Port_Emp WHERE FK_Dept='@MySysPara' . \n - How to pass in system parameters: please refer to the method Flow_SaveParas(workid, paras) for the flow attribute, flow 2 open, call: Flow_SaveParas(workid, paras) . \n #### Summary expressions are divided into three categories. \n - Login information: @WebUser.No, @WebUser.DeptNo, @WebUser.OrgNo \n - Node form fields: @MyFieldName.\n - Parameters passed from the system: by calling the API. Call: Flow_SaveParas(workid, paras) method. \n #### Other. \n - What is ccbpm expression, please baidu: ccbpm expression. \n - Note: 1. case sensitive. 2. order cannot be changed, No,Name \n",
