            _key9:
              '\n #### Help \n - Video Tutorials: https://drive.weixin.qq.com/s?k=AOsAZQczAAYgmfqbFS\n - Definition: A form permission scheme is where a form has different permissions that need to be controlled on different nodes, we call this a form permission scheme. \n - For example: the start node is editable, the 2nd node is read-only, and the 3rd node is editable for the department field. Such a scenario can be defined using a permission scheme. \n #### Default Scenario \n - The form is rendered to the operator according to the permissions of the form at the time of designing the form. \n\n #### Reference Process \n - Demonstrates the process: 014.Project Approval Process. \n - This process binds multiple forms, and at each node, the bound forms have different permissions. \n 1401 node, the bound form is the default solution and can be edited. \n 1402 node, the bound form is a read-only scheme, the recipient can only view the form, can not edit the content of the form fields. \n 1403 node, the bound form is a custom form permission, the recipient can edit the form according to the set form elements, including fields within the form, from the table, attachments and so on. \n 1404 node, the bound table unit is a read-only scheme. \n #### Configuration Diagram \n - ! [Enter image description](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/FrmSln/Sln5/Img/FrmCtrlSlnSetting1.png "Screenshot.png") \n - ! [Enter image description](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/FrmSln/Sln5/Img/FrmCtrlSlnSetting4.png "Screenshot.png") \n - ! [Enter image description](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/FrmSln/Sln5/Img/FrmCtrlSlnSetting2.png "Screenshot.png") \n - ! [Enter image description](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/FrmSln/Sln5/Img/FrmCtrlSlnSetting3.png "Screenshot.png") \n',
