            _key16:
              '\n \n #### Help \n - Show node-bound forms when they have data. \n - All nodes of a process are bound to 10 forms, 1 form is filled in at the beginning of the node collection, the other 9 forms have no data. \n #### Application Scenario \n - A tax office has 10 operations, each of these 10 operations has a different form, but each of the business processes is exactly the same (initiation-audit-feedback). \n #### Design Process \n - When designing a process, simply design a process that creates 10 business forms with 10 forms bound to each node. \n - Set the initiation pre-navigation in the process properties of the process, set it to [counted according to the individual forms bound at the start node], please refer to the process properties for initiation pre-navigation. \n - In each node form enable rule of the process, the start node is all set to be enabled with parameters, and the other nodes are set to be enabled with data. \n - Please refer to process 026. \n #### Running Effects - Front Navigation Launch Process \n - ! [Enter image caption](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/FrmSln/Sln5/Img/RoleDate.png "Screenshot.png")\n #### Running Effects - Launching Flow \n - ! [Input image caption](. /resource/WF/Admin/AttrNode/FrmSln/Sln5/Img/RoleDate2.png "Screenshot.png")\n \n #### Other Notes \n - Starting a node to invoke a process can also be done without using the front navigation, or you can use the parameter mode to invoke the form. \n - e.g.: Start Administrative Penalty Flow /WF/MyFlow.htm?FK_Flow=001&Frms=Frm_XZCF\n - e.g.: Start Project Application Flow /WF/MyFlow.htm?FK_Flow=001&Frms=Frm_A,Frm_B,Frm_C\n',
