          '\n    <div>\n      <h2>Clarification：</h2>\n   <p>1. Detection limitations: Please note that due to the complexity of internal and external environments, our QA procedures cannot provide 100% assurance that there are no issues in the process design.</p>\n          <p>2. Problem classification: The QA program categorizes detected problems into the following three levels for your better understanding and handling:</p>\n          <ul>\n            <li><strong style="color: green">text</strong>：Record node detection information without affecting process operation.</li>\n            <li><strong style="color: #dada88">Warning</strong>：More serious problems, adjusted according to the actual situation, recommended for attention but not necessarily for immediate modification, without affecting the functioning of the process.</li>\n            <li><strong style="color: red">Error</strong>：Serious problem, must be <span style="color: red">immediately modified!</span>，Failure to do so may affect the functioning of the process.</li>\n          </ul>\n          <p>3. Error Handling: For "Error" level issues, they represent actual errors in the operation of the program and must be corrected immediately to ensure the accuracy and effectiveness of the process design.</p>\n          <p>4. Auto-correction: CCBPM system is equipped with auto-correction function, which is able to recognize and automatically fix the wrong part of the system settings to reduce your workload.</p>\n          <p>5. Data table structure repair: In addition, CCBPM also has the ability to automatically repair the data table structure to ensure the consistency and integrity of the data to further enhance the stability and reliability of process design.</p>\n        </div>\n      ',
