          '\n #### Help \n - Forms in the form repository are called standalone forms, each of which can be bound to any node of any process. \n - A form is similar to a carriage that stays in the repository and can be used only if he is bound to a node. \n - Each node is analogous to a locomotive, a locomotive can hang multiple carriages or one carriage. \n - A node hangs a single form, which we call a single form process, and multiple forms are called a form tree process. \n - Permission Control for Forms: A node hooked up to a form has permission control over the overall form to be read-only, visible, and editable, and can control the state characteristics of each form element. \n #### Legend -1\n ! [Enter image caption](. /resource/WF/Admin/Img/Tree1.png "Screenshot.png") \n #### Legend -2\n ! [Enter image caption](. /resource/WF/Admin/Img/Tree.png "screenshot.png") \n\n ',
        _key38:
          '\n #### Help \n - SDK form is ccbpm the interface presentation is completely handed over to the developer to deal with, the developer only need to design a form, add a send button, call ccbpm send API can be completed \n - the rendering of the form are completed by the developer, the operation of the process can be done by calling a different interface. \n - This mode is adapted to more complex forms but ccform can not meet the requirements of the user in the case of using sdk form. \n - For more information about this form, please refer to: Process Attributes\\ Development Interfaces. \n ! [Enter image description](. /resource/WF/Admin/Img/SDKFrm.png "Screenshot.png") \n ',
        _key39:
          '\n #### Help \n - You can define a page that binds to this node. \n - There is a Save() function inside the page, which will be triggered when the user clicks the [Save] button or [Send] button on the toolbar outside the frame. \n - You need to complete the data integrity validation and data saving in the Save() function. \n - Return true if the save succeeds, return false if the save fails. e.g.: when the user performs a send, the save is performed first, the save succeeds, then the send is performed, and when the save fails, the send is blocked. \n - The url you enter can have parameters, but the system will attach all the parameters to the url. \n - For example:/SDKFlowDemo/QingJia/SDKQianRuFangShiForm.htm . \n - For example:The url you configured is http://xxxx:222:/abc.htm The actual Url of the system is http://xxxx:222:/abc.htm?FK_Flow=xxx&FK_Node=xxx&WorkID=xxx&UserNo=xxx&Token=xxx\n - The system will take the current flow environment as the url. The system will pass the variables and parameters in the current process environment to your customized page, you can display, save and control the data according to these parameters, the data is read-only and editable. \n - If you use absolute path you can use ccbpm global variable @SDKFromServHost , for example: @SDKFromServHost/MyFile.htm\n\n #### Sample 1\n ! [Enter image description](. /resource/WF/Admin/Img/SelfFrm.png "Screenshot.png") \n\n #### Sample 2\n ! [Input Image Description](. /resource/WF/Admin/Img/SDKFrm.png "Screenshot.png") \n ',
