      glodbsrchelper: {
        _key1:
          '\n ##### Background Explanation \n - Formats recognized by ccfast: No,Name,ParentNo, Explanation: No=Code column, Name=Tag name column, ParentNo=Code of the parent node. \n - If the format returned by the other party does not match, it is necessary to set the conversion property so that ccfast can recognize it. \n - For example: API call returns BianHao,MingCheng,FuBianHao column. \n - you need to set BianHao in [Number attribute No] and MingCheng in [Name attribute Name]. ##### Overview \n - Convert the dictionary format returned by the other side to a format that ccfast can recognize. \n ',
        _key2:
          "{'\n    ##### Parameter format\n    - For objects that need to be parameterized for data testing.\n    - Individual parameter format: @ParaKey=123\n    - Multiple parameter formats: @ParaKey1=123@ParaKey2=456\n    #### About aliases\n    - Parameter names, aliases can be used as parameters.\n    - Before using an alias, you need to set up an alias, see Setting up an alias.\n    ##### Clarification\n     - The parameters of the data source are built-in parameters and do not need to be passed in, e.g., Token.\n    '}",
        _key3:
          "{'\n ##### POST content. \n - valid for Post access format. \n - Parameter format e.g. {Send: '@WebUser.No','WorkID':@WorkID} \n - Parameter format 2: {'Token':'@Token'} token is a constant for the datasource, which can be configured in the datasource properties. \n - Parameter aliases: When defining a procedure the name of the parameter is defined as @JE,@WorkID, when in use the name of the corresponding parameter may change then you need to use the parameter aliases, for example: \n - @JE=JinE,JiaGe@WorkID=OID, etc. \n #### What is the body of the call? \n - The object that uses the dictionary is the calling body, the calling body is roughly: master table populated, slave table populated, data source entity. \n '}",
        _key4:
          "{'\n ##### For: Get format \n - Enter full name, parameters are allowed in address: /xxx.do?userID=@WebUser.No&tike=@Token&workID=@WorkID&ndID=@NodeID&je=@JinE\n - Parameters are divided into system parameters and custom parameters. \n - System Parameters: Information about the person who logged in, such as：@WebUser.No Login Personnel Account,@WebUser.Name Name,@WebUser.DeptNo Department number,@WebUser.OrgNo Organization Number, @Token token.\n - Custom Parameters: &je=@JE Amount is a custom parameter. \n ##### For: Post Format \n - Fill Format: /xxx.do\n - Parameters are provided through Post content. \n '}",
        _key5:
          "{'\n    ##### For: Get format \n     -  Enter the full name, parameters are allowed in the address: http://127.0.0.1:9000/xxx.do?userID=@WebUser.No&tike=@Token&workID=@WorkID&ndID=@NodeID&je=@JinE\n     -  Parameters are divided into system parameters and customized parameters.\n     -  System Parameters: Information about the logged in person, e.g.:@WebUser.No Login Personnel Account,@WebUser.Name Name,@WebUser.DeptNo Department number,@WebUser.OrgNo Organization number, @Token token.\n     -  Customized parameters: &je=@JE   The amount is a customized parameter.\n    ##### For: Post specification\n     - Filling Format：http://127.0.0.1:9000/xxx.do\n     - Parameters are provided via the Post content.\n     #### Returned data format requirements:\n     - execute correctly\n      { code:200, message:'Implementation success',data:'json or string data' }\n     - misbehave\n     { code:500, message:'implementation error',data:'json or string data' }\n\n    '}",
        _key6:
          '\n ##### Description \n - valid for post ,get. \n ##### Format \n - Fill in the format: {key1:\'xxxx\',key2:\'x33xxx\'}\n #### Example \n {\n "Token":"@Token",\n "md5":"@md5"\n }\n ##### Special note \n - Use half quotes. \n ',
        _key7:
          "{'\n #### Definitions \n - The Key of the parameter is generic. Key1 and Key2 are equal,\n - Expression 1: SELECT * FROM XXX WHERE XinShui > @JE AND RecNo='@WebUser.No'\n - Expression 2: /WF/API/Demo_XXX?JE=@JinE&NianLing=@NianLing\n - The parameter key passed in scenario A is JE, in scenario B is JineE, in order to keep the commonality of both parameters key. Scenario A the incoming parameter is JE, in Scenario B it is JineE, in order to maintain the commonality of the two parameter keys. \n - Setting format: JE=JineE,MyJE,NianLing=Age,NL\n - Separate each parameter with a comma. Key=Key1,Key2\n '}",
        _key8:
          '\n #### Definition \n - During the execution of the webapi, if under the returned root node is the data that needs to be obtained, then this attribute remains empty. \n - If the returned data is under the specified node, then the name of the node needs to be filled in. \n #### Example \n - If the result returned in the webApi dictionary is {} then there is no need to set this attribute. \n - If the result returned is contents:{ } then the data is under the contents node and you need to set contents to this option. \n',
      },
