            '\n #### Help \n - Blank fields: used to load the form when its data source is obtained from a dictionary of parameters. \n - For example, the form consists of four drop-down fields: Area, Province, City, District. When the form is loaded, the value of the other three fields cannot be determined without identifying the area. \n - provinces, regions, districts and counties will need to be bound to a blank data source foreign key. \n - Use cascading relationships to implement data cascading queries to the other field data. \n ',
