          _key21:
            "\n #### Help \n - Please select a foreign key dictionary table, if there is not one please create one on the left. \n - To create a foreign key field, you must select a dictionary table for the foreign key. \n - Listed are dictionaries without parameters. \n\n #### About Foreign Key Dictionary Tables \n - Data that has a code, a name we call a dictionary table, for example: area, province, tax type, tax headings, department. \n - To create a foreign key dictionary table you must rely on a data source. \n - Data obtained from other systems, \n - Foreign Key Dictionary Tables can be linked to \n\n #### Dictionary Data Source Types \n - SQL Statements: obtained from relational databases. \n - WebApi: obtained from web services. \n - Javascript: obtained from script's function method. \n - ccform built-in data maintenance, maintains dictionaries in the ccbpm system. \n\n #### two formats data format \n - number name format: e.g. district, province. \n - Tree structure format: e.g. department, catalogue tree. \n #### Types of data sources \n - Relational databases \n - Web services. \n\n ",
          _key22:
            '\n #### Help \n - Selection of enumeration for enumeration library. \n - If you do not have the data, click Enumeration Library Management to create a new enumeration. \n #### Definitions. \n - Enumeration is divided into int type and string type. \n - Enumeration of type Int: political profile, 0=Mass 1=Regiment member, 2=Party member. \n - Enumeration of type String: political profile, qz=masses ty=reunionists, dy=party members. \n - Enumeration format (Item separated by comma): leave of absence, sick leave, marriage leave, others \n\n #### Enumeration storage \n - Enumeration master table: Sys_EnumMain \n - Enumeration slave table: Sys_Enum\n ',
          _key23:
            '\n #### Help \n - Fill in the format: enumeration value=enumeration label; \n - e.g.: ty=Regimentary, dy=Party member, qz=Masses, 2=Party member, 2=Party member. For example: ty=Regiment member, dy=Party member, qz=Mass person\n - The system parses this as: ty is a member of the regiment, dy is a member of the party, qz is a member of the mass person. \n\n #### Data storage. \n - A string enumeration is also known as a tagged enumeration, where letters are stored in a column and tags are stored in a column. \n - In a form where the field is abc, then the system automatically creates a shadow field abcT.\n - The abc field stores the tags, abcT stores the labels. \n - This is consistent with the external data source storage. \n ',

